commit.title: [Evarutil.reachable_from_evars : evar_map -> Evar.Set.t -> Evar.Set.t]
commit.message:
[Evarutil.reachable_from_evars : evar_map -> Evar.Set.t -> Evar.Set.t]

The new primitive [Evarutil.reachable_from_evars sigma seeds] computes
the transitive closure of evars accessible from [seeds] by aliasing, as
requested by Enrico. We still use it lazyly in check_evars, so in
cases where the tactic did not introduce new evars we don't need to
compute it.
